=== Post-Viral Respiratory Syndrome Recognition

The COVID-19 pandemic revealed that 51% of Long COVID patients meeting PEM criteria satisfied ME/CFS diagnostic criteria @Komaroff2023, establishing ME/CFS as a common outcome of post-viral syndromes following respiratory infections. This pattern extends beyond SARS-CoV-2:
    - 40.3% of SARS-CoV-1 survivors developed unexplained chronic fatigue
    - 27% of SARS-CoV-1 survivors fulfilled CFS diagnostic criteria
    - Post-influenza, post-pneumonia, and post-mononucleosis chronic fatigue syndromes share overlapping features
Pneumologists treating respiratory infection survivors are positioned to:
    - Identify early who is at risk for chronic sequelae
    - Implement preventive rest protocols during acute illness
    - Recognize when referral to ME/CFS specialists is appropriate
    - Apply two-day CPET for objective documentation


